# class TreeNode:
#     def __init__(self, val=0, left=None, right=None):

class Solution:
    def isSameTree(self, p: Optional[TreeNode], q: Optional[TreeNode]) -> bool:
        if not p and not q:
            return True
        if not p or not q:
            return False
        
        que = deque([p,q])
        
        while que:
            cur1 = que.popleft()
            cur2 = que.popleft()
            if not cur1 and not cur2:
                continue

            if not cur1 or not cur2 or cur1.val != cur2.val:
                return False
            
            que.append(cur1.left)
            que.append(cur2.left)
            que.append(cur1.right)
            que.append(cur2.right)
        return True

class Solution {
    public List<List<Integer>> verticalTraversal(TreeNode root) {
        List<int[]> nodes = new ArrayList<int[]>();
        dfs(root, 0, 0, nodes);
        Collections.sort(nodes, new Comparator<int[]>() {
            public int compare(int[] tuple1, int[] tuple2) {
                if (tuple1[0] != tuple2[0]) {
                    return tuple1[0] - tuple2[0];
                } else if (tuple1[1] != tuple2[1]) {
                    return tuple1[1] - tuple2[1];
                } else {
                    return tuple1[2] - tuple2[2];
                }
            }
        });
        List<List<Integer>> ans = new ArrayList<List<Integer>>();
        int size = 0;
        int lastcol = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        for (int[] tuple : nodes) {
            int col = tuple[0], row = tuple[1], value = tuple[2];
            if (col != lastcol) {
                lastcol = col;
                ans.add(new ArrayList<Integer>());
                size++;
            }
            ans.get(size - 1).add(value);
        }
        return ans;
    }

    public void dfs(TreeNode node, int row, int col, List<int[]> nodes) {
        if (node == null) {
            return;
        }
        nodes.add(new int[]{col, row, node.val});
        dfs(node.left, row + 1, col - 1, nodes);
        dfs(node.right, row + 1, col + 1, nodes);
    }
}

class CustomStack(object):

    # : O(1)
    # : O(n)
    def __init__(self, maxSize):
        """
        :type maxSize: int
        """
        self.stack = [0] * maxSize
        self.top = -1
        
    # : O(1)
    # : O(n)
    def push(self, x):
        """
        :type x: int
        :rtype: None
        """
        if self.top < len(self.stack) - 1:
            self.top += 1
            self.stack[self.top] = x
        
     # : O(1)
    # : O(n)
    def pop(self):
        """
        :rtype: int
        """
        if self.top == -1:
            return -1
        value = self.stack[self.top]
        self.top -= 1
        return value
        
    # : O(k)
    # : O(n)
    def increment(self, k, val):
        """
        :type k: int
        :type val: int
        :rtype: None
        """
        lim = min(k, self.top + 1)
        for i in range(lim):
            self.stack[i] += val

class Solution(object):
    def decodeString(self, s):
        """
        :type s: str
        :rtype: str
        """
        stack, res, multi = [], "", 0
        for c in s:
            if c == '[':
                stack.append([multi, res])
                res, multi = "", 0
            elif c == ']':
                cur_multi, last_res = stack.pop()
                res = last_res + cur_multi * res
            elif '0' <= c <= '9':
                multi = multi * 10 + int(c)
            else:
                res += c
        return res

class Solution:
    def sortedListToBST(self, head: Optional[ListNode]) -> Optional[TreeNode]:
        def getLength(head: ListNode) -> int:
            count = 0
            while head:
                count += 1
                head = head.next
            return count

        def buildBST(left: int, right: int) -> TreeNode:
            if left > right:
                return None
            m = (left + right) // 2
            root = TreeNode()
            left_node = buildBST(left, m - 1)
            nonlocal head
            root.val = head.val
            head = head.next
            
            right_node = buildBST(m+1, right)
            root.left = left_node
            root.right = right_node
            return root

        l = getLength(head)
        return buildBST(0, l - 1)

class LRUCache:
    class Node:
        def __init__(self, key: int, val: int):
            self.key = key
            self.val = val
            self.pre = pre
            self.next = next

    def __init__(self, capacity: int):
        self.capacity = capacity
        self.dummy = self.Node(-1, -1)
        self.dummy.pre = self.dummy
        self.dummy.next = self.dummy
        self.map = {}

    def add_node_to_head(self, node: Node):
        node.pre = self.dummy
        node.next = self.dummy.next
        self.dummy.next.pre = node
        self.dummy.next = node

    def remove_node(self, node: Node):
        node.pre.next = node.next
        node.next.pre = node.pre

    def get(self, key: int) -> int:
        if key not in self.map:
            return -1

        node = self.map[key]
        self.remove_node(node)
        self.add_node_to_head(node)
        return node.val

    def put(self, key: int, value: int) -> None:
        if key in self.map:
            node = self.map[key]
            node.val = value
            self.remove_node(node)
            self.add_node_to_head(node)
            return

        new_node = self.Node(key, value)
        self.map[key] = new_node
        self.add_node_to_head(new_node)

        if len(self.map) > self.capacity:
            tail = self.dummy.pre
            del self.map[tail.key]
            self.remove_node(tail)

    def detectCycle(self, head: Optional[ListNode]) -> Optional[ListNode]:
        if not head or not head.next:
            return None

        slow, fast = head, head
        while fast:
            slow = slow.next
            fast = fast.next.next if fast.next else None
            if slow and slow == fast:
                fast = head 
                while fast != slow:
                    fast = fast.next
                    slow = slow.next
                return fast

```python
class ListNode:
    def __init__(self, key, value):
        self.key = key
        self.val = value
        self.next = None
        self.pre = None

class LRUCache:
    def __init__(self, capacity: int):
        self.capacity = capacity
        self.length = 0
        self.head = ListNode(None, None)
        self.tail = ListNode(None, None)
        self.head.next = self.tail
        self.tail.pre = self.head
        self.map = {}

    def _add_to_head(self, key: int, value: int):
        node = ListNode(key, value)
        node.next = self.head.next
        self.head.next = node
        node.next.pre = node
        node.pre = self.head
        self.map[key] = node
        self.length += 1

    def _remove_from_tail(self, key: int):
        remove_key = self.tail.pre.key
        self.tail.pre = self.tail.pre.pre
        self.tail.pre.next = self.tail
        self.map.pop(remove_key)
        self.length -= 1

    def _move_node_to_head(self, node: ListNode):
        node.pre.next = node.next
        node.next.pre = node.pre
        self.head.next.pre = node
        node.pre = self.head
        node.next = self.head.next
        self.head.next = node
        
    def get(self, key: int) -> int:
        if key in self.map:
            node = self.map[key]
            self._move_node_to_head(node)
            return self.map[key].val
        return -1
        
    def put(self, key: int, value: int) -> None:
        node = self.map.get(key)
        if node:
            self._move_node_to_head(node)
            node.val = value
        else:
            if self.length >= self.capacity:
                self._remove_from_tail(key)            
            self._add_to_head(key, value)
```

#     def __init__(self, val=0, left=None, right=None):
#         self.val = val
#         self.left = left

class Solution:
    def findBottomLeftValue(self, root: Optional[TreeNode]) -> int:
        q = deque()
        res = (root,0)
        q.append((root,0))
        while q:
            node, level = q.popleft()
            cur_level = res[1]
            if level > cur_level:
                res = (node, level)

            if node.left:
                q.append((node.left, level+1))
            if node.right:
                q.append((node.right, level+1))

        return res[0].val

class Solution:
    def findBottomLeftValue(self, root: Optional[TreeNode]) -> int:
        def dfs(node, cur_depth, leftmost, depthest):
            if cur_depth > depthest:
                leftmost = node.val
                depthest = cur_depth

            if node.left:
                leftmost, depthest = dfs(node.left, cur_depth+1, leftmost, depthest)
            if node.right:
                leftmost, depthest = dfs(node.right, cur_depth+1, leftmost, depthest)
            return leftmost, depthest

        leftmost, depthest = dfs(root, 1, root.val, 1)
        return leftmost

class Solution:
    def lengthOfLongestSubstring(self, s: str) -> int:
        max_str = 0
        left = 0
        right = 0
        seen = set()
        while right < len(s):
            while s[right] in seen:
                seen.remove(s[left])
                left += 1
            seen.add(s[right])
            right += 1
            max_str = max(max_str, right-left)
        return max_str

class Solution:
    def findSubstring(self, s: str, words: List[str]) -> List[int]:
        word_len = len(words[0])
        word_count = len(words)
        total_len = word_len * word_count
        target_counter = Counter(words)
        res = []

        for i in range(word_len):
            left = i
            window_counter = Counter()
            count = 0

            for j in range(i, len(s) - word_len + 1, word_len):
                word = s[j:j+word_len]
                if word in target_counter:
                    window_counter[word] += 1
                    count += 1

                    while window_counter[word] > target_counter[word]:
                        left_word = s[left:left+word_len]
                        window_counter[left_word] -= 1
                        count -= 1
                        left += word_len

                    if count == word_count:
                        res.append(left)

                else:
                    window_counter.clear()
                    count = 0
                    left = j + word_len

        return res

class Solution:
    def rotateRight(self, head: Optional[ListNode], k: int) -> Optional[ListNode]:
        if not head or not head.next:
            return head
        tail = head
        length = 1
        while tail.next:
            length += 1
            tail = tail.next
        tail.next = head

        k = k % length
        for _ in range(length - k):
            tail = tail.next
        
        head = tail.next
        tail.next = None
        return head

class MyQueue:

    def __init__(self):
        """
        inpushoutpop
        """
        self.stack_in = []
        self.stack_out = []


    def push(self, x: int) -> None:
        """
        inpush
        """
        self.stack_in.append(x)


    def pop(self) -> int:
        """
        Removes the element from in front of queue and returns that element.
        """
        if self.empty():
            return None
        
        if self.stack_out:
            return self.stack_out.pop()
        else:
            for i in range(len(self.stack_in)):
                self.stack_out.append(self.stack_in.pop())
            return self.stack_out.pop()


    def peek(self) -> int:
        """
        Get the front element.
        """
        ans = self.pop()
        self.stack_out.append(ans)
        return ans


    def empty(self) -> bool:
        """
        inout
        """
        return not (self.stack_in or self.stack_out)

            return 1

        max_of_left = [0] * n
        max_of_left[0] = arr[0]
        for i in range(1, n):
            max_of_left[i] = max(max_of_left[i-1], arr[i])

        min_of_right = [0] * n
        min_of_right[n-1] = arr[n-1]
        for i in range(n-2, -1, -1):
            min_of_right[i] = min(min_of_right[i+1], arr[i])

        # 3.

        #  arr[i+1...n-1] 
        chunks = 0
        for i in range(n - 1):
            if max_of_left[i] <= min_of_right[i+1]:
                chunks += 1

        #  =  + 1
        return chunks + 1

class DLinkedNode:
    def __init__(self, key=0, value=0):
        self.key = key
        self.value = value
        self.prev = None
        self.next = None

class LRUCache:
    def __init__(self, capacity: int):
        self.cache = dict()
        self.capacity = capacity
        # 
        self.head = DLinkedNode()
        self.tail = DLinkedNode()
        self.head.next = self.tail
        self.tail.prev = self.head

    def _add_to_head(self, node: DLinkedNode):
        # 
        node.prev = self.head
        node.next = self.head.next
        self.head.next.prev = node
        self.head.next = node

    def _remove_node(self, node: DLinkedNode):
        # 
        node.prev.next = node.next
        node.next.prev = node.prev

    def _move_to_head(self, node: DLinkedNode):
        # 
        self._remove_node(node)
        self._add_to_head(node)

    def get(self, key: int) -> int:
        if key not in self.cache:
            return -1
        
        node = self.cache[key]
        # 
        self._move_to_head(node)
        return node.value

    def put(self, key: int, value: int) -> None:
        if key in self.cache:
            #  key 
            node = self.cache[key]
            node.value = value
            self._move_to_head(node)
        else:
            #  key 
            if len(self.cache) == self.capacity:
                # 
                removed_node = self.tail.prev
                self._remove_node(removed_node)
                # 
                del self.cache[removed_node.key]

            # 
            new_node = DLinkedNode(key, value)
            self._add_to_head(new_node)
            self.cache[key] = new_node

class Codec:

    def serialize(self, root):
        """Encodes a tree to a single string.
        
        :type root: TreeNode
        :rtype: str
        """
        res = []
        def dfs(node):
            if not node:
                res.append("null")
                return
            res.append(str(node.val))
            dfs(node.left)
            dfs(node.right)
        
        dfs(root)
        return ",".join(res)

    def deserialize(self, data):
        """Decodes your encoded data to tree.
        
        :type data: str
        :rtype: TreeNode
        """
        if not data:
            return None

        return build_tree()

from typing import List, Optional
import collections

class Solution:
    def verticalTraversal(self, root: Optional[TreeNode]) -> List[List[int]]:
        if not root:
            return []
            
        # 1. 
        #  BFS  (col, row, val)
        nodes_info = []
        queue = collections.deque([(root, 0, 0)]) # (node, row, col)
        
        while queue:
            node, row, col = queue.popleft()
            nodes_info.append((col, row, node.val))
            
            if node.left:
                queue.append((node.left, row + 1, col - 1))
            if node.right:
                queue.append((node.right, row + 1, col + 1))
        
        # 2. 
        # 
        # Python 
        nodes_info.sort()
        
        # 3. 
        # 
        result_map = collections.OrderedDict()
        for col, row, val in nodes_info:
            if col not in result_map:
                result_map[col] = []
            result_map[col].append(val)
            
        return list(result_map.values())

from typing import List

class Solution:
    def topKFrequent(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> List[int]:
        if not nums:
            return []
        
        # -----------------------------------------------------------------
        #  1: 
        # -----------------------------------------------------------------
        
        # a. 
        min_val = min(nums)
        max_val = max(nums)
        
        # b. 
        offset = -min_val
        
        # c. 
        count_array_size = max_val - min_val + 1
        count_array = [0] * count_array_size
        
        # d. 
        for num in nums:
            #  num 
            index = num + offset
            count_array[index] += 1

        # -----------------------------------------------------------------
        #  2:  K 
        # -----------------------------------------------------------------

        # a. 
        #  len(nums) + 1
        buckets = [[] for _ in range(len(nums) + 1)]

        # b. 
        for i in range(count_array_size):
            freq = count_array[i]
            if freq > 0:
                #  i 
                num = i - offset
                buckets[freq].append(num)

        # -----------------------------------------------------------------
        #  3: 
        # -----------------------------------------------------------------
        
        result = []
        # 
        for i in range(len(buckets) - 1, 0, -1):
            # 
            if buckets[i]:
                # 
                result.extend(buckets[i])
            
            # 
            if len(result) >= k:
                break
        
        #  k k
        return result[:k]

import collections
import heapq
from typing import List

class Solution:
    def topKFrequent(self, nums: List[int], k: int) -> List[int]:
        # 1. O(N)
        freq_map = collections.Counter(nums)
        
        # 2.  k O(M log k)M
        min_heap = []
        for num, freq in freq_map.items():
            # Pythonheapq(, )
            # 
            heapq.heappush(min_heap, (freq, num))
            if len(min_heap) > k:
                heapq.heappop(min_heap) # pop out
        
        # 3. 
        # kk
        result = [item[1] for item in min_heap]
        return result

import collections
from typing import List

class Solution:
    def findSubstring(self, s: str, words: List[str]) -> List[int]:
        if not s or not words:
            return []

        word_len = len(words[0])
        num_words = len(words)
        total_len = word_len * num_words
        words_freq = collections.Counter(words)
        result = []

        #  word_len 
        for i in range(word_len):
            left = i  # 
            seen = collections.Counter() # 
            count = 0 # 

            #  word_len 
            for j in range(i, len(s) - word_len + 1, word_len):
                word = s[j : j + word_len]
                
                if word in words_freq:
                    seen[word] += 1
                    count += 1
                    
                    # 
                    while seen[word] > words_freq[word]:
                        left_word = s[left : left + word_len]
                        seen[left_word] -= 1
                        count -= 1
                        left += word_len
                    
                    # 
                    if count == num_words:
                        result.append(left)
                        # 
                        left_word = s[left : left + word_len]
                        seen[left_word] -= 1
                        count -= 1
                        left += word_len

                else:
                    #  words 
                    # 
                    seen.clear()
                    count = 0
                    left = j + word_len
        
        return result

from typing import List

class Solution:
    def minSubarray(self, nums: List[int], p: int) -> int:
        n = len(nums)
        # 1. 
        target_rem = sum(nums) % p
        
        #  p 
        if target_rem == 0:
            return 0
        
        # 2.  {: }
        #  {0: -1} 
        rem_map = {0: -1}
        min_len = n  # 
        
        # 3.  current_sum 
        current_sum = 0
        
        for i, num in enumerate(nums):
            current_sum += num
            current_rem = current_sum % p
            
            # 
            needed_rem = (current_rem - target_rem + p) % p
            
            # 
            if needed_rem in rem_map:
                prev_index = rem_map[needed_rem]
                # 
                min_len = min(min_len, i - prev_index)
            
            # 
            rem_map[current_rem] = i
            
        #  min_len n
        # 
        return min_len if min_len < n else -1
